{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2825a04b-f9bb-4b02-99cf-010c2cbeaadc","content":"Here's what I found in `my_app/views.py`:\n\n**Line 3:** `datetime.now()` — hard-coded static call, impossible to freeze/mock cleanly in tests.\n\n### Recommendation\n\nInject the clock dependency via Django's `django.utils.timezone.now`, which is the standard Django approach and easily patchable:\n\n```python\nfrom django.utils import timezone\n\ndef index(request):\n    now = timezone.now()\n    return render(request, 'index.html', {'time': now})\n```\n\n**Why it matters:**\n- `datetime.now()` returns a naive datetime (no timezone) — a bug in timezone-aware Django projects.\n- `timezone.now()` is a single, well-known function you can mock in tests with `freezegun` or `unittest.mock.patch`.\n\nThis was the only file in `my_app/`. Want me to apply the fix?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ffd99653-730b-40d8-9f64-dde26bf84a2f","outputTokens":212,"requestId":"5C31:1BEBDD:20A5228:259E272:69F5617F"},"id":"9171fe78-a021-4906-94a9-12dd1d8662c4","timestamp":"2026-05-02T02:29:25.661Z","parentId":"58d9410e-9a56-4857-9e2e-b2587774dadc"}
